text: The Digital Transformation Office (DTO) was an Australian Federal Government agency formed on . The office was in charge of digitizing and managing various government services. On it was superseded by the Digital Transformation Agency. While active it was primarily responsible for managing the myGov service. == References == Category:Government agencies established in 2015 Category:2015 establishments in Australia Category:Defunct Commonwealth Government agencies of Australia Category:2016 disestablishments in Australia
